A motorbike rider has been killed and seven others sustained injuries ranging from minor to serious on Wednesday morning after a taxi and motorbike collided on Modderfontein and Greenstone drive in Greenstone Hill.
,
ER24 Spokesperson Ineke van Huyssteen said when paramedics arrived on the scene just before 7 am they found seven patients who sustained minor to serious injuries.
“A male motorbike rider was found lying a few metres away from his motorbike. Unfortunately, he sustained fatal injuries and was declared dead on the scene,” Van Huyssteen said.
The injured were treated before they were taken to a hospital.
Authorities are probing the cause of the fatal crash.
– African News Agency (ANA)
